==Cover songs==

{|
|valign=top|
===Covers appearing on albums===
* "Where Were You Last Night" by [[Ankie Bagger]] (on "[[Wish I Had an Angel]]" single)
* "High Hopes (Live cover)" by [[Pink Floyd]] (on ''[[Highest Hopes]]'' compilation)
* "[[Walking in the Air]]", theme song from ''[[The Snowman]]'' by [[Howard Blake]] (on ''[[Oceanborn]]'' album) 
* "Phantom of the Opera" by [[Andrew Lloyd Webber]] (on ''[[Century Child]]'' album)
* "Symphony of Destruction (Live cover)" by [[Megadeth]] (on "[[The Siren (song)|The Siren]]" single)
* "Over the Hills and Far Away" by [[Gary Moore]] (on ''[[Over the Hills and Far Away (album)|Over the Hills and Far Away]]'' EP)
* "Crimson Tide (Live cover)" by [[Hans Zimmer]] (on ''[[From Wishes to Eternity]]'' live album)
* "Deep Blue Sea (Live cover)" by [[Trevor Rabin]] (on ''[[From Wishes to Eternity]]'' live album)
|valign=top|

===Covers only played live===
* "Crazy Train" by [[Ozzy Osbourne]]<ref name="metalfanb">{{cite web | title=Metalfan.nl | work=Een interview met Tuomas Holopainen van Nightwish | url=http://www.metalfan.nl/interviews.php?id=13 | accessmonthday=December 30 | accessyear=2005}}</ref>
* "Wild Child" by [[W.A.S.P.]]<ref name="metalkings">{{cite web | title=MetalKings.ru | work=NIGHTWISH 27.09.03 Moscow | url=http://metalkings.ru/reviews/gigreports/nightwish-gig-270903.htm | accessmonthday=December 29 | accessyear=2005}}</ref> (appears on [[End of Innocence]] DVD)
* "Don't Talk to Strangers" by [[Dio]]<ref name="darktales">{{cite web | title=Dark Tales | work=NIGHTWISH – 11.01.2003 – Oberhausen “König Pilsener Arena” | url=http://www.dark-tales.com/Konzerte/2003/Nightwish/nightwish.html | accessmonthday=December 29 | accessyear=2005}}</ref>
